    course_description = '<div class="introduction" id="introduction"><p>The Graduate Certificate of Accounting suits students with various aspirations, including:</p><p>1. Graduates with no background in accounting who can study concepts and techniques in accounting without enrolling in a full Masters program.</p><p>2. Graduates with prior accounting studies who wish to develop advanced knowledge in accounting without enrolling in a full Masters program.</p><p>3. Graduates with prior accounting studies who need up to four more courses to fully satisfy the admission requirements of the Australian professional accounting bodies.</p><p>The Graduate Certificate program is designed to articulate into the Master programs in accounting. Students who wish to continue their advanced studies and complete the Graduate Certificate with a GPA of 4.0 may apply for admission to the Master of Applied Accounting. Those with a GPA of 4.5 may apply for admission to the Master of Professional Accounting or the Master of Accounting.</p><p>The program is taught by research active academic staff. Students are exposed to professional and scholarly academic research in commerce, enhancing their academic and professional competence.</p></div>',
